channel.title: Source issues | Need help
channel.description:
I am having issues with a server source i just downloaded:
Server viewed here: http://www.moparisthebest.com/smf/index.php/topic,532756.0.html
I was wondering if anyone could help me out with the issue? Issue: http://imageshack.us/photo/my-images/607/63263316.png/
I have edited the source's compiler to JDK1.7.0_02 but the run.bat is different to the usual run.bat's that i see. It seems to have JDK not JRE so I'm not quite sure if that is an issue or not.
I am not an experienced coder and this may just be a minor issue, but I dont really know and I probably sound retarded asking. Any help would be high appreciated.
Thanks -Beast

item.title: Source issues | Need help
item.dc:creator: @zyle1992 Zymus
item.description:
@zyle1992 wrote:

Post the contents of your run.bat file

EDIT: Nevermind. I didnt read the error correctly. Hyperion and Hyperion based servers have the JAGGRAB server implemented and are able to transfer the cache data from the server. The problem youre having is that the files that are to be readuex by the server, or the archive that is being requested by the cloent does not exist, or is in the wrong directory.
